channel.desc: Where curious cooks become confident cooks.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Pasta all' amatriciana is perhaps Rome's most famous dish. Despite the fancy name, it's nothing more than long-strand pasta sauced with tomatoes, onion, bacon, and hot pepper flakes and dusted with cheese. We show you how to master this simple dish.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Bridget uncovers the secrets for making perfect Pasta e Ceci. Next, Jack challenges Julia to a tasting of parmesan. Then, Dan reveals the science behind parmesan’s signature flavor. Finally, Elle shows Bridget how to make the ultimate Penne Arrabbiata.

programme.title: Cook's Country
programme.desc: Bridget shares steps to achieving perfect Memphis-style Wet Ribs in the Slow Cooker. Next, Jack challenges Julia to an apple-cider vinegar tasting. And finally, Ashley teaches Bridget how to make the leftover favorite, Mashed Potato Cakes from scratch.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Few recipes deliver so much pleasure for so little work as pancakes. The batter comes together in minutes, and the cooking time is brief. Why, then, do most Americans never make pancakes from scratch?

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Bridget and Julia prepare tacos dorados and Lisa reviews fire extinguishers. Dan then gives a demonstration of fast-freezing liquid nitrogen, and Erin makes roasted poblano and black bean enchiladas for Bridget.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.sub-title: Fried Rice and Kung Pao Shrimp
programme.desc: We show you how to prepare fried rice and kung pao shrimp. Our findings of rice cookers and long-grain white rice guarantee perfect rice every time.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Lemon Bundt cake, glazed with a snowy white icing, is an elegant dessert but is often lacking in lemon flavor. Key lime pie is another favorite, but transporting this pie and it's wobbly filling, can be tricky. We set out to solve both these problems.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Boneless pork chops are lean and quick-cooking, making them ideal for weeknight meals. Pork tenderloin, which is also lean, has a somewhat fussy reputation, but you don't need to be a professional chef to cook tenderloin properly.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: On a hot summer's day, life doesn't get much better than a big, juicy, smoky slab of spicy, mouth-watering ribs. Our goal was to produce flavorful, juicy, tender ribs that would be well worth the time, money, and effort.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Dan makes Bridget Sous Vide Seared Steaks. Adam then reviews his top pick for sous vide machines, and Elle makes a show stopping sous vide staple: Soft-Poached Eggs.

programme.title: Cook's Country
programme.desc: Bridget and Julia cook up Tennessee Pulled Turkey Sandwiches. Then, Adam reviews paper towels. Next, Jack challenges Bridget to a tasting of extra-sharp cheddar cheese. And finally, Bryan shows Bridget a recipe for Eastern North Carolina Fish Stew.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.sub-title: To Meat or Not to Meat (Sauce)
programme.desc: Bridget and Julia demonstrate the best weeknight Tagliatelle with Bolognese Sauce. Jack challenges Bridget to a tasting of crushed tomatoes. Dan explains why you can’t overcook mushrooms. Finally, Becky makes Julia the ultimate Meatless “Meat” Sauce.

programme.title: Cook's Country
programme.desc: Ashley makes Bridget perfect Fish and Chips. Then, Jack challenges Julia to a tasting of hamburger buns. And finally, Christie makes Julia the ultimate Shrimp Burgers.

programme.title: Cook's Country
programme.desc: Bryan and Bridget reveal the secrets to making a Southern California classic, Smoked Fish Tacos. Next, Adam shows Julia his top pick of chimney starters. Finally, Christie makes Julia the perfect Grilled Steak Fajitas.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: Julia goes into the test kitchen with Bridget to reveal the secrets to making Home-Corned Beef with Vegetables. Then, Jack challenges Bridget to a tasting of sherry vinegar. Finally, Elle shows Julia how to make the ultimate Snickerdoodles.

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen

programme.title: America's Test Kitchen
programme.desc: We prepare a Thai-inspired beef stir-fry and share a recipe for great potstickers.

channel.desc: No existe el "crimen perfecto", descubre por qué en Forensic Files en Español, donde investigadores de la vida real reúnen la evidencia necesaria para resolver crímenes atroces sacados directamente de los titulares de periódicos.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Aunque su hija ha escapado antes, ella siempre ha regresado. Sus padres estaban seguros que esta vez no sería diferente, pero estaban equivocados.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La víctima era un hombre que se forjó a sí mismo que nunca medía sus palabras. Quizás fue asesinado por un cliente o empleado descontento. Tal vez las fotos picantes en su caja fuerte tenían la pista para resolver el crimen.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Las cámaras de seguridad en un casino rastrearon los movimientos de una joven poco antes de que desapareciera. Nunca se le volvió a ver, pero a través de la evidencia que dejó, pudo decírsele a los investigadores qué le sucedió y quién fue el responsable.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La policía obtiene una pista sobre una pareja que desapareció en el fin de semana de Memorial Day (Día Conmemorativo) en un robo en marcha. La evidencia que se encuentra resuelve el crimen brutal.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Un guardia de seguridad desapareció de su puesto sin dejar rastro; sus restos fueron encontrados un año después en un campamento remoto.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En el 2001, Ginger Hayes y su pequeño hijo fueron secuestrados durante un robo de auto. El crimen había sido reportado por un testigo a los pocos minutos de ocurrir.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En el 2002, el director de la funeraria Lonnie Turner, Sr., fue encontrado muerto a tiros. Su hijo, Lonnie Jr., se convirtió en el principal sospechoso, particularmente después de que se descubrió que el asesinato se cometió con su arma.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En un poco más de un mes, dos mujeres que han vivido en el mismo complejo de apartamentos fueron brutalmente asesinadas.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La escena del crimen fue especialmente violenta: un esposo y una esposa fueron asesinados a tiros en su habitación. ¿Fue cómplice su hija de 16 años?

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: El sospechoso principal tenía un historial criminal y su licencia de conducir se encontró en la escena del crimen de un homicidio doble brutal.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La esposa de un oficial de policía muy respetado es asesinada en su propio hogar. El crimen se fue sin resolver por más de una década, hasta que una nueva unidad de casos del pasado sin cerrar se forma le toma un nuevo vistazo a la evidencia.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Cuando se encuentra un carro en una zanja de drenaje con dos cuerpos adentro, una punta de un dedo de un guante de látex apuntaría a los investigadores a tanto la escena del crimen como al asesino.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos

channel.desc: Join the crew of the Straw Hat Pirates and set a course for anime adventure with One Piece. The global phenomenon is now a 24/7 channel on Pluto TV.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: I won't kick even if it costs me my life! Sanji's chivalry!
programme.desc: Luffy runs into trouble trying to sail his way to Robin, Usopp and Zoro end up handcuffed together, and Sanji’s inability to kick a women may lead to serious injury!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Fukurou's miscalculation! My cola is the water of life!
programme.desc: Chimney and Gombe show Luffy the secret passage that leads to Robin, and Franky puts on a display of raw punching power thanks to a few bottles of cola!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Zoro busts out a new technique! The sword's name is sniper king?
programme.desc: While Franky’s brawl spills into the ocean, Usopp and Sanji attempt to overcome their handcuffs by outsmarting their opponents!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.desc: Determined not to be defeated by the heinous hair of a devious lion, Chopper risks life and limb by summoning the power of his Rumble Ball for a third time!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Boss luffy returns! Is it a dream or reality? Lottery ruckus!
programme.desc: Travel back to ancient Japan for a madcap adventure starring the Straw Hats, some old friends and enemies, and a camel that eats lottery tickets!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: A big rice cake tossing race at the castle! Red nose's plot!
programme.desc: The madcap throwback continues as Luffy and the gang – along with a crowd of characters from the Alabasta arc – competes for a priceless treasure hidden inside a tasty snack!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Bubble master kalifa! The soap trap closes in on nami!
programme.desc: Nami battles a bathing beauty and her lethal bubbles, Chopper unleashes his inner beast, and Luffy inches ever closer to catching up with Robin!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Resounding bad news! Buster call invoked!
programme.desc: Franky has a painful encounter with monster Chopper, and Nami gets scrubbed too clean to fight! Meanwhile, Spandam accidentally invokes the deadly Buster Call!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Five namis? Nami strikes back with mirages!
programme.desc: Zoro uses Usopp as a decoy in his battle with the beasts, and Nami discovers the secret that could be the key to survival in her brawl with the bathing beauty!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Nami's decision! Fire at the out-of-control chopper!
programme.desc: Franky and Nami come up with a plan to stop Chopper’s rampage, but it could prove deadly to the not-so-little reindeer. Usopp and Zoro are thrilled to finally be free of each other!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Hunter sanji makes an entrance? Elegy for a lying wolf!
programme.desc: Usopp’s ill-advised attempt at bravery threatens to get him killed, but a familiar foot spares the sniper’s life. Luffy struggles to even strike a formidable foe, and Franky races to deliver some very important keys!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Fiery kicks! Sanji's full course of foot techniques!
programme.desc: Sanji evens the playing field in his CP9 slugfest by introducing his wolfish opponent to the burning power of the devil’s leg!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Fierce sword attacks! Zoro vs. Kaku, powerful sword fighting showdown!
programme.desc: Zoro finally lands a blow against the killer giraffe, but Luffy still can’t find a way to break through against Lucci! Can Frank reach Robin before it’s too late!?

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Demon god zoro! An incarnation of asura born from fighting spirit!
programme.desc: Zoro unleashes a demonic nine sword fighting style on his giraffe opponent, Luffy buys time for Franky by ascending to second gear, and Robin refuses to give up hope of being rescued!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Spandam frightened! The hero on the tower of law!
programme.desc: Spandam cruely drags Robin ever closer to the gates of justice, but the battle takes a turn for the better when the Sniper King makes a surprise appearance!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Robin freed! Luffy vs. Lucci, showdown between leaders!
programme.desc: Luffy’s battle with Lucci reveals the powerful secrets of the rubber man’s second gear, and the Spandam’s thoughtless Buster Call begins with a brutal barrage of cannonballs.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Boss luffy is the culprit? Track down the missing great cherry tree!
programme.desc: When an ancient tree is stolen by a madman with the power to freeze time, Luffy, Usopp, and Sanji track down the culprit in an attempt to save a village’s annual festival!
